text: On tap, at Oblivion Bar and Grill, with the same crowd, pours a copper orange color. Taste is winter spices, with cinnamon , nutmeg, allspice and apple pie....absolutely phoenominal . Taste is full of the above mentioned spices and apple pie. Finishes on the same tasting notes with a sweet pumpkin fiinish. Quaff Score 8 /10

On tap at Oblivion Taproom in Orlando. Pours a Copperbelt orange with an off white head and nice pumpkin spice, cinnamon aroma. Taste is full of pumpkin pie throughout, lots of nice fall spices coming through- cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, leading to a pumpkin pie spices finish. Delicious and very drinkable pumpkin brew

On tap @ Tampa Bay Brewing. Rich amber colored beer with a thin white head. Huge vanilla and clove. Quite intense. A good bit of ginger and nutmeg as well. The flavor and mouthfeel have a little bit of that grainy, dried spice quality to it, but pretty smooth and creamy otherwise. Good sweetness of caramel and toasted malts. Solid pumpkin beer, if you like that sort of thing.

Pours a brown-amber with a medium light tan head. Aroma is something akin to pumpkin pie & root beer. The individual spices within the aroma are latent but beautiful with nutmeg & clove - smells awesome. Taste is identical and smooth. This is not as sweet as it smells, but the spices are definitely the stars. I dont get pumpkin and not necessarily pumpkin pie either, but I do get something appropriate for the season. Well done and unique.

Growler during RBWG. Pours a clear copper orange with small white head. The aroma is cinnamon and spice. Thin mouth, light spice and pumpkin, sugary finish, one of the best all around pumpkin beers ive ever tried.
Amazing aroma of sweet sugary pumpkin pie. Not actual pumpkin, but I get the idea of pumpkin. A great beer, nonetheless

On tap at TBBC. Nose is pumpkin pie, cinnamon, nutmeg, clove, caramel. Pours a cloudy orange. Flavor is almost buttery with tons of cinnamon and nutmeg but not too much. Balanced sweetness. Very nice.

On draft at Cajun Cafe Fall Beer Fest 2013. Pours a nice hazy orange color with a white head. Distributor poured me a glass of foam and I had to let it settle. Nose is some candied pumpkin, some light pie spices, some sweet malt, and some sugar. Flavor is similar with roasted pumpkin, some pie spices, some sugar, and some light ginger. Medium in body and a nice pumpkin beer overall.

Draft at Brass Tap Trinity. Pours a dark ruby brown with a small white head. Sweet aroma with hints of vanilla, nutmeg and other spices. Flavor has a ton of vanilla up front tollwed by almond and a nice mixture of spices: nutmeg, cinnamon, and clove.

Growler... RBWG 2013 This beer rocks! Dirty orange ale with a small, tight, off-white head. The spice-rack aroma is a swirl of nutmeg, cinnamon, chai tea, graham and pumpkin meat. Medium to full-bodied with an oily mouthfeel and tingly carbonation. The flavor is pretty much what this beers nose promised  loads of spice-rack and gourdy goodness. Well-balanced  not overly sweet or overly bitter. Finishes toasty and spicy. Big-time thanks goes out to burg326 for sharing this exceptional pumpkin beer!
Aroma is sweet pumpkin pie, appearance is dark amber, taste is pumpkin and nutmeg spices but not overly sweet.
@RBWG-JAX Grand Tasting-offwhite-amber. A-nutmeg, pumpkin, med malt. T-nutmeg bite, pumpkin, med malt.
Growler during RBWG 2013. Amber pour with a small khaki head. Lots of pumpkin spice in the nose and flavor, but a fair amount of pumpkin and caramel sweetness to back it up. Not bad.
Copper pour with white head and lace. Aroma is vanilla and pumkin pie. Flavor is vanilla, pumpkin, and some other pleasant flavor. Medium bodied with no carbonation.

growler provided by burg236, thanks for all the beer you bought!! .. . pours out a mild amber .. mild lacing and head .. . interesting stuff, its like eating a thanksgiving candle .. . slight linger in my mouth .. . pretty tasty pumpkin beer, up there with some of the best .. . . i made wine out of raisins so i wouldnt have to wait for it to age.

Growler shared at RBWG thanks to burg326! Pours a translucent copper with nice bubbly tan head and moderate lacing. Aroma of nice pumpkin pie with vanilla back. Taste follows, nice nutmeg, cinnamon, and vanilla notes. On par with CCB Good Gourd, one of the best pumpkin beers I have had, and held up well.

Growler thanks to, you guessed it, burg326 at the RBWG Grand Tasting Jax, FL.   Pours  a watered down amber with a small off white head.  Nose  shows sweet potato, gourd, pumpkin, light cinnamon and brown sugar.  Flavor is similar--this is easily the best pumpkin tasting beer I have had.  I might still enjoy parcela more for its funky JP yeast, but this beer had incredibly nice pumpkin/gourd fruit flavor without being too bitter or vegetal, or what have you.  Sounds like others liked it as well.

Growler thanks to, you guessed it, burg326 at the RBWG Grand Tasting Jax, FL. Poured a low haze, brighter orange. Thick, white head. Nose is exceptional carrot cake, bourbon, buttercream frosting, walnut, allspice, nutmeg. Oh yeah. Taste is rich carrot cake, frosting. Carrot cake the beer essentially. Denser, oily palate. Yummy.

Growler to taster at the RBWG Grand Tasting (thanks burg326). Looks good; a cloudy brown with off-white lacing. Smells good; an awesome pumpkin and spice flavor. Tastes like it smells with a good mouthfeel. An outstanding example of the style.

Growler at RBWG 2013 Grand Tasting. Pours clear amber with a large, frothy head. Tons of autumn spices and fresh pumpkin pie on the nose, medium to big sweet flavor, lots of balanced but robust pumpkin pie, nutmeg, bready malts. Medium bodied with fine carbonation. Sweet finish, more fall spices,naresh pumpkin. Well balanced. Damn tasty.

Color was a dark red with a small white head. Aroma was spiced and sweet, mostly a sugary nutmeg. Taste is nutmeg and cinnamon with a nice level of sweetness, but too much spice. Palate was a little watery and would have been enhanced by a little more carbonation.

Great pumpkin from Tampa. Pint pour, deep amber with one finger head. Aroma is rich, sweet pumpkin, vanilla, caramel, toffee, harvesty spices. Flavor is similar, rich and smooth. Vanilla and burnt sugar in the back, pumpkin all over. Nicely spiced, but not too heavily. Lighter body, no lacing. Very well done.

Very good local pumpkin beer. Even though its more sweet and spicy then what I expected.          

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On draft at the Brass Tap, poured a deep brown/orangish color, aromas of pumpkin, spice, light nutmeg, and some sugar.  Flavors are the same light sweetness on the palate, not overly pumpkiny, but has a little of crust, and some light roasted malt to it as well.  A nice interpretation of this style, could easily drink this all day with out getting sick of it.
